ine ants (2002) Ecology, 83, pp. 1610-1619; Knaden, M., Wehner, R., Nest mark orientation in desert ants Cataglyphis: what does it do to the path integrator? (2005) Anim. Behav., 70, pp. 1349-1354; Kronfeld-Schor, N., Dayan, T., Partitioning of time as an ecological resource (2003) Annu. Rev. Ecol. Syst., 34, pp. 153-181; Lenoir, A., Aron, S., Cerdá, X., Hefetz, A., Cataglyphis desert ants: a good model for evolutionary biology in Darwin's anniversary year - a review (2009) Isr. J. Entomol., 39, pp. 1-32; Narendra, A., Reid, S.F., Hemmi, J.M., The twilight zone: ambient light levels trigger activity in primitive ants (2010) Proc. Biol. Sci., 277, pp. 1531-1538; Nuss, A., Suiter, D., Bermett, G., Continuous monitoring of the black carpenter ant, Camponotus pennsylvanicus (Hymenoptera : Formicidae), trail behavior (2005) Sociobiology, 45, pp. 597-618; Orr, M., Parasitic flies (Diptera: Phoridae) influence foraging rhythms and caste division of labor in the leaf-cutter ant, Atta cephalotes (Hymenoptera: Formicidae) (1992) Behav. Ecol. Sociobiol., 30, pp. 395-402; Ranganathan, Y., Ghara, M., Borges, R., Temporal associations in fig-wasp-ant interactions: diel and phenological patterns (2010) Entomol. Exp. Appl., 137, pp. 50-61; Ronacher, B., Path integration as the basic navigation mechanism of the desert ant Cataglyphis fortis (Forel, 1902) (Hymenoptera: Formicidae) (2008) Myrmecol. News, 11, pp. 53-62; Ruano, F., Tinaut, A., Soler, A.J.J., High surface temperatures select for individual foraging in ants (2000) Behav. Ecol., 11, pp. 396-404; Thomas, M.L., Holway, D.A., Condition-specific competition between invasive Argentine ants and Australian Iridomyrmex (2005) J. Anim. Ecol., 74, pp. 532-542; Wehner, R., The architecture of the desert ant's navigational toolkit (Hymenoptera: Formicidae) (2009) Myrmecol. News, 12, pp. 85-96; Wehner, R., Lanfranconi, B., What do the ants know about the rotation of the sky? (1981) Nature, 293, pp. 731-733; Whitford, W.G., Depree, D.J.